info.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 28 at 11:49AM PST until January 30 at 1:00PM PST by NWS Eureka
info.description: ...WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 1 PM SUNDAY TO 1 PM PST MONDAY... * WHAT...Northeast winds 10 to 20 mph with gusts up to 45 mph expected. * WHERE...Southern Humboldt Interior, Northern Trinity, Southern Trinity, Northwestern Mendocino Interior, Northeastern Mendocino Interior, Southeastern Mendocino Interior, Northern Lake and Southern Lake Counties. * WHEN...From 1 PM Sunday to 1 PM PST Monday. * IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result.
info.instruction: Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.
